  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Senior Planner",
  "description": "<p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Develop, maintain, and update detailed project schedules across all project phases (design, procurement, construction, testing &amp; commissioning, handover) using software such as Primavera P6, Microsoft Project, or equivalent.</li>\n  <li>Collaborate with project managers, engineers, and subcontractors to gather inputs for schedule development and progress updates.</li>\n  <li>Ensure that schedules reflect all critical activities including design, procurement, construction, testing &amp; commissioning, and handover phases.</li>\n  <li>Perform critical path analysis, schedule risk assessment, and resource loading where necessary.</li>\n  <li>Track and report progress against baseline schedules and flag deviations or delays to relevant stakeholders.</li>\n  <li>Support in preparation of weekly and monthly reports, including look-ahead schedules and recovery plans.</li>\n  <li>Integrate subcontractor schedules into the master schedule and maintain alignment with overall project objectives.</li>\n  <li>Participate in regular progress meetings, contribute to forecasting, and planning discussions.</li>\n  <li>Assist in the development and maintenance of project-specific Work Breakdown Structure (WBS) and activity coding.</li>\n  <li>Coordinate with cost control teams to align schedule with budget and cost forecasts.</li>\n  <li>Support claims and extension of time (EOT) analysis through schedule analysis when required.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Requirements</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Degree/Diploma with at least 3 years of experience in project scheduling/planning support, preferably in data centre or critical environment.</li>\n  <li>Knowledge of scheduling tools such as Primavera P6 or Microsoft Project.</li>\n  <li>Understanding of project lifecycle, construction sequencing, and commissioning processes.</li>\n  <li>Familiarity with construction sequences and project lifecycles.</li>\n  <li>Certification in workplace safety (eg. WSQ, WSH) preferred.</li>\n  <li>Positive proactive attitude and ethical behaviour.</li>\n  <li>Team player with ability to work independently and resolve challenges in a fast-paced environment.</li>\n  <li>Excellent interpersonal, communication and collaborative skills.</li>\n  <li>Proficiency in Microsoft Office (Microsoft Word, Excel and PowerPoint).</li>\n</ul>",
